{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a4df0308-84b0-40a1-b8c2-b2e1a736e1ca","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll provide general guidance on migrating to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC).\n\n## Key Changes\n\n**1. Add `id-token: write` permission to your job:**\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**2. Replace your `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n\n```yaml\n# Before (API key):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# After (trusted publishing):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nNo `--api-key` needed — the OIDC token is used automatically once configured.\n\n**3. Add the NuGet service connection setup step** (before push):\n\n```yaml\n- name: Authenticate with NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget update source nuget.org --valid-authentication-types token\n```\n\nOr use the `dotnet/trusted-publishing` action if available for your setup.\n\n**4. Configure NuGet.org side:**\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://nuget.org) → your package → **Manage** → **Trusted Publishers**, add a GitHub Actions policy specifying:\n- Repository owner/name\n- Branch/tag pattern (e.g., `refs/tags/v*`)\n- Optionally the workflow filename and environment\n\n**5. (Recommended) Use a GitHub environment:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    environment: nuget-publish\n    ...\n```\n\nThis gives you an extra layer of control and pairs with NuGet's trusted publisher config.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The workflow changes are minimal (add `id-token` permission, remove `--api-key`), but you must register your repo as a trusted publisher on nuget.org first. After that, you can delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"80aaf1aa-30c3-48ae-945b-4a632b22d319","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no existing workflow file to look at. The user is asking a general question about switching from API key-based NuGet publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. I'll provide guidance based on the standard approach.","outputTokens":559,"requestId":"1027:BF033:28B8299:2D091FF:69FD34A1"},"id":"b3e03eda-6f1e-4c7d-87d6-8ad5651fb1c9","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:28.733Z","parentId":"4038f0f6-99eb-4b0d-90ae-4f2d45d2a653"}
